components.name: React Components
components.description: Reusable UI elements that manage their own state and can be composed to build complex user interfaces.

components.name: ReactDOM
components.description: A package that provides DOM-specific methods that can be used at the top level of a web app to enable an efficient rendering of React components.

components.name: Babel Compiler
components.description: A JavaScript compiler that transforms JSX and modern JavaScript syntax into a format compatible with older browsers.

components.name: Webpack
components.description: A module bundler that compiles JavaScript modules and assets, optimizing them for deployment.

data_flows.description: React components render their output to the DOM through ReactDOM, allowing for dynamic updates to the UI.
Babel processes JSX and modern JavaScript code, which is then bundled by Webpack for deployment.

trust_boundaries.name: Client-Side Trust Boundary
trust_boundaries.description: The boundary between the user's browser and the server, where user inputs are processed and rendered.

trust_boundaries.name: Build Process Trust Boundary
trust_boundaries.description: The boundary during the build process where code is transformed and bundled before deployment.
